headline: US Stock Market Today: S&P 500 Futures Slip as Yields Stay Stubbornly High
summary: The Morning Bull - US Market Morning Update Friday, Nov, 14 2025 US stock futures are pointing lower this morning, with S&P 500 contracts down about 0.38 percent and Nasdaq futures sliding nearly 0.7 percent. The biggest catalyst weighing on sentiment is the stubbornly high US 10-year Treasury yield, which remains above 4.1 percent. headline: Stock Index Futures Plunge on Fed Rate-Cut Doubts and Valuation Concerns
summary: December S&P 500 E-Mini futures (ESZ25) are down -0.97%, and December Nasdaq 100 E-Mini futures (NQZ25) are down -1.29% this morning, pointing to further losses on Wall Street as worries over stretched tech valuations persisted and investors questioned whether the Federal Reserve was still on track to cut rates in December.
